(Netcare 911) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A hot air balloon carrying at least 14 people has crashed near the Buffelspoort dam in the North West, injuring two adults and a child. - Are you there? Send us your eyewitness accounts and photos.Netcare 911 said one adult is in a critical condition and another sustained moderate injuries. They were stabilised at the scene before being transported to nearby hospitals. A Netcare helicopter was sent to the scene to airlift a 4-year-old child to a Johannesburg hospital. "The child is being flown to a level 1 trauma facility in Johannesburg that caters for the intensive care of children under the age of 16 years old who have been subjected to serious physical trauma," Netcare said.The cause of the accident is still being investigated.&nbsp;3 people seriously injured after Hot Air Balloon crashes into tree, North West https://t.co/PPSfxIbmLB #ArriveAlive @Netcare911_sa pic.twitter.com/1elSoBJlyP&mdash; Arrive Alive (@_ArriveAlive) October 25, 2016Netcare2 airlifts an injured child from Buffelsfontein in the North West after a Hot Air Balloon crashed into a tree pic.twitter.com/Mcxx4mSQjB&mdash; Netcare911 (@Netcare911_sa) October 25, 20163 people seriously injured after Hot Air Balloon crashes into tree, North West https://t.co/PPSfxIbmLB #ArriveAlive @Netcare911_sa pic.twitter.com/1elSoBJlyPNetcare2 airlifts an injured child from Buffelsfontein in the North West after a Hot Air Balloon crashed into a tree pic.twitter.com/Mcxx4mSQjB24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.